COMPREHENSIVE (LOSS) INCOME. AVERAGE YIELD ON NON-TAXABLE INVESTMENT SECURITIES IS CALCULATED ON A TAX-EQUIVALENT BASIS USING THE U.S. FEDERAL STATUTORY TAX RATE OF 35 PERCENT.

(E)

AMOUNTS INCLUDE (I) AVERAGE EQUITY SECURITIES BALANCES, WHICH ARE INCLUDED IN INVESTMENT SECURITIES ON THE CONSOLIDATED BALANCE SHEETS, AND (II) THE

ASSOCIATED DIVIDEND INCOME. THE AVERAGE YIELD ON OTHER ASSETS HAS NOT BEEN SHOWN AS IT WOULD NOT BE MEANINGFUL.

(F)

THE AVERAGE YIELD ON TOTAL INTEREST-EARNING ASSETS IS ADJUSTED FOR THE IMPACTS OF ITEMS MENTIONED IN (D) ABOVE.

(G)

INCLUDES PREMISES AND EQUIPMENT, NET OF ACCUMULATED DEPRECIATION AND AMORTIZATION.

